{"key":"processedPost-11925953","value":{"id":11925953,"first":11920196,"last":12010162,"when":1264815850,"utime":"01/30/10 03:44 AM","content":"You want roughly 100' to 125' lineal per minute leaving the front of your filter.(fpm)&nbsp; All of this math has been posted in many threads already and they're available at the top of the page via the 'search posts' icon.&nbsp; This means that for a 2 square foot filter, you want 200 to 250 cubic feet per minute(cfm)&nbsp; For a four square foot filter, you want 400 to 500 cfm.&nbsp; This cfm needs to be at the static pressure the filter was designed to operate at.&nbsp; Always add ten to twenty percent for losses due to friction, turns, prefilter, etc.<br />RR","title":"Re: help with choosing HEPA filter size?","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}